ed8f3662-c860-4d88-be96-9220129c6984.012c0c72-af33-41a7-ab85-5091b418a214.description=This subflow queries the InfraDB to select the CCNAME from Cloudcell based on the datacell acronym. inpput\: server.1.datacenter The acronym in the datacenter table ed8f3662-c860-4d88-be96-9220129c6984.034d8c95-f24b-4656-98bf-30616c51a9f2.description=Generic flow to send an e-mail ed8f3662-c860-4d88-be96-9220129c6984.8899622b-43a4-4675-93bb-992a840e9759.description=
This operation is used to retrieve a value from a list. When the index of an element from a list is known, this operation can be used to extract the element.

Inputs\:
    list - A list to get the value from.
    delimiter - The delimiter that separates values in the list.
Default value\: ','
    index - The index of the value (starting at 0) to retrieve from the list.
Valid values\: an integer, end (for the last element), end-1 (for the second to last element)

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. It contains the value found at the specified index in the list, if the value specified for the "index" input field is positive and less than the size of the list. Otherwise, it contains the value specified for "index".

Responses\:
     success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
     failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.

Inputs\: _PROCESS_INSTANCE_ID - Process Instance Id _processInstanceState - Process Instance State (Use value from selection list CSA-ProcessInstance-State) Result\: _processInstanceState -Updated Process Instance State ed8f3662-c860-4d88-be96-9220129c6984.90dd35a7-43d7-4f73-bbd3-bcd6bd69b70e.description=
Generate Run URL - Generates an href HTML link that contains a URL to the run history report for the current run.

Inputs\:
    variablename  - The name of the flow variable where the result should be stored.
Default value\: IC_ReportURL
    displaytext - The text to display for the href link. 
Default\: "Run History Report Available Here"

Results\:
    result - The untagged URL to the run report for the current run.
Example (with default values)\: IC_ReportURL ,Run History Report Available Here

Responses\:
    success - The flow completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The flow completed unsuccessfully.

The flow takes the first child component id and identifies it as the primary server id. This id is updated on the server group component as value of the property “primaryServerId”. This step is performed in this flow, because subscription related information is obtained with a subflow requiring a server id as input. The primary server id will also be needed later on for updating disk information in infradb. The flow “DB_ReserveClustername” then calls the function RFK_GETCLUSTERNAME with the required inputs to register a new cluster name with the subscription id in the CCLUSTER table. ed8f3662-c860-4d88-be96-9220129c6984.ea26112f-8e84-4d80-a66d-c897012d9338.description=This workflow updates the Process Instance State using PEM API.
